This paper is about human pose estimation using deep learning, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new method that uses explicit 2D features and intermediate 3D representations, which suggests that it may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a network architecture, which suggests that it may fall under graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
